sql:
SELECT product_id, SUM(quantity) AS Total_Quantity_Sold 
FROM customer_purchases 
WHERE product_id = 0;

SELECT DISTINCT customer_id
FROM customer_interactions
WHERE interaction_date >= DATE('now', '-1 year');

external_knowledge:
- "wandering souls in the market" refers to customers; 
- "reflections in the world of commerce" refer to their purchases (product ID, quantity, total price); 
- "echoes in the chambers of interaction" alludes to their interactions (interaction type, description); 
- "banners of campaigns" symbolizes the marketing campaigns associated with their segment; 
- "whispers of performance" indicates the campaign performance metrics.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM customer_purchases 
WHERE customer_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id)
FROM customer_purchases
WHERE total_price > 500;

SELECT DISTINCT c.customer_id, c.first_name, c.last_name
FROM customers c
JOIN customer_purchases cp ON c.customer_id = cp.customer_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'voyagers' refers to customers who have made purchases;
- 'journey of commerce' means the process of making purchases;
- 'names, identities' correspond to the first name, last name, and customer ID;
- 'treasures they have scattered' refers to the total amount spent;
- 'societal groups' refers to the segment name.
